}}
}}

==Other in-source locations==
{{More|Wikipedia:Citing sources#Sound recordings}}
Often, a page number is not appropriate such as when citing an audio or video source or a book that has no page numbers. The {{cs1}} templates have an {{para|at}} parameter that can be used to include non-page locators. The [[:Category:Pages and Categories from Wikipedia 2]][[Category:Author-date citation templates|Author-date citation templates]] use {{para|loc}}.

Some example locators: section (sec.), column (col.), paragraph (para.); track; hours, minutes and seconds; act, scene, canto, book, part, folio, stanza, back cover, liner notes, indicia, colophon, dust jacket, verse

